<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"Conclusion-Potentialimprovementsandbugs">Potential improvements a=
nd bugs</h2>
<p>We now have a basic interface but it already has some bugs and it could =
be improved in a lots of ways. Here is a list of things that are left as ex=
ercises:</p>
<ul>
<li>Improve the look and feel and output: it's partially of done in commit =
<a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ExtendingPlatformUIConferenceBundle=
/commit/13d5a0b2f4d957425a751a2cc4cbd6566ed0b57a" class=3D"external-link" r=
el=3D"nofollow">13d5a0b2</a> but can probably improved further.</li>
<li>Reload only the table, not the full view when filtering.</li>
<li>Sorting.</li>
<li>More filters, more columns, etc.</li>
<li>The server side code deserves to be refactored.</li>
<li>Unit tests.</li>
<li><strong>[bug]</strong> Highlight is buggy in navigation because we have=
 several routes while the navigation item added in<span class=3D"plugin_pag=
etree_children_span"><a href=3D"/display/TECHDOC/Configure+the+navigation">=
 Configure the navigation</a> only recognizes the first route we add.</span=
></li>
<li><strong>[bug]</strong> 'eng-GB' hardcoded when getting Content Type nam=
e.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"Conclusion-Documentationpagestogofurther">Documentation pages to =
go further</h2>
<p>This tutorial talks and uses a lots of concepts coming from Symfony, eZ =
Platform, PlatformUI itself or YUI. Here is a list of documentation pages t=
hat are worth reading to completely understand what's going on behind the s=
cenes:</p>
<h3 id=3D"Conclusion-Symfony-relateddocumentationpages">Symfony-related doc=
umentation pages</h3>
<ul>
<li>From a Symfony point of view, in this tutorial we mainly wrote a contro=
ller and with the associated routing configuration, <a href=3D"http://symfo=
ny.com/doc/current/book/controller.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nof=
ollow">the Controller book page</a> is definitively the most important Symf=
ony related page to read</li>
<li>We also defined a Controller as a service in this tutorial, this is det=
ailed in <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/cookbook/controller/serv=
ice.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">How to Define Controller=
s as Services</a>.</li>
<li><p><a href=3D"http://twig.sensiolabs.org/doc/templates.html" class=3D"e=
xternal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Twig for Template Designers</a> explains how=
 to write Twig templates</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Conclusion-eZPlatform-relateddocumentationpages">eZ Platform-rela=
ted documentation pages</h3>
<ul>
<li>The Public API is described in both the <a href=3D"/display/TECHDOC/Pub=
lic+API+basics">Public API basics page</a> and in <a href=3D"/display/TECHD=
OC/Public+API+Cookbook">the Public API Cookbook</a>.</li>
<li>For any usage beyond what is covered in those pages, you can refer to <=
a href=3D"http://apidoc.ez.no/sami/trunk/NS/html/index.html" class=3D"exter=
nal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">the auto-generated API doc</a>.</li>
<li>While extending PlatformUI, you'll also have to work with <a href=3D"ht=
tps://doc.ez.no/display/TECHDOC/REST+API+Tutorials" rel=3D"nofollow">the RE=
ST API which has its own section in the documentation</a>.</li>
<li>There is also <a href=3D"http://ezsystems.github.io/javascript-rest-cli=
ent/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">an auto-generated API doc fo=
r the JavaScript REST Client</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Conclusion-PlatformUI-relateddocumentationpages">PlatformUI-relat=
ed documentation pages</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/TECHDOC/Backend+interface" rel=3D"=
nofollow">The PlatformUI technical introduction</a> gives an overview of th=
e architecture and explains some its concepts.</li>
<li>PlaformUI also has <a href=3D"http://ezsystems.github.io/platformui-jav=
ascript-api/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">an auto-generated AP=
I doc</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Conclusion-YUI-relateddocumentationpages">YUI-related documentati=
on pages</h3>
<p>The whole YUI documentation could be useful when working with PlatformUI=
, but amongst others things here is a list of the most important pages:</p>
<ul>
<li>For the very low level foundations, the guides about <a href=3D"http://=
yuilibrary.com/yui/docs/attribute/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow=
">Attribute</a> and <a href=3D"http://yuilibrary.com/yui/docs/base/" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Base</a> (almost everything in Platform=
UI is YUI Base object with attributes), <a href=3D"http://yuilibrary.com/yu=
i/docs/event-custom/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">EventTarget<=
/a> (custom events) and <a href=3D"http://yuilibrary.com/yui/docs/plugin/" =
class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Plugin</a> (for tweaking almost an=
y PlatformUI components) can be very useful</li>
<li>A large part of the application is about manipulating the DOM and subsc=
ribing to DOM events, this is covered in the <a href=3D"http://yuilibrary.c=
om/yui/docs/node/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Node</a> and <a=
 href=3D"http://yuilibrary.com/yui/docs/event/" class=3D"external-link" rel=
=3D"nofollow">DOM Events</a> guides.</li>
<li>The PlatformUI Application is based on the YUI App Framework which itse=
lf is mainly described in <a href=3D"http://yuilibrary.com/yui/docs/app/" c=
lass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">the App Framework</a>, <a href=3D"h=
ttp://yuilibrary.com/yui/docs/router/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofol=
low">Router</a> and <a href=3D"http://yuilibrary.com/yui/docs/view/" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">View</a> guides.</li>
</ul>
    </div>
